    "display_name": "Call Me Maybe",
    "long_instructions": "You’ve been given the vocals for a song, but no backing tracks! This is a great time to organize your code using **abstraction**, so each section of the remix is clean, simple, and easy to understand.\r\n\r\n**Your task:** Create one function for each vocal section. Inside each function, add unique backing tracks that match the mood and rhythm of that part. Then call your functions to play the full remix.\r\n\r\nWhen you're finished, your code should look similar to this:\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/5b9ea6223e507c03eff4cef75ef3daa4-image-1742271918560.png)",
    "bubble_choice_description": "Create unique backing tracks for each vocal section of the song using functions to keep things organized",
